It is truly curious, indeed, to observe the univer- sality of this fashion of applying unguenta to the whole, or the greater part of the body among man- kind, in every age, and every state of society. At the very time that it thus prodigally prevailed among the polite and voluptuous nations of Greece and Rome, it was equally in vogue among the barbarous inhabitants of Britain. Nor have modern adventurers discovered the existence of any people whatsoever, where it has not been found a custom established im- memorially amongst them.
